page.title: 02Streetly Cub Camp
page.content: On the 21st June we, the 31st Streetly Cub pack went to the Beaudesert camp site at Gentleshaw. Nearly all our cub pack went. When everybody was there we went into our tents and unloaded our kit. Afterwards one of our leaders called Woody and I helped to build a swing and then we played on it. Then we went down to the woods and went into the rododendron bushes and Budgie said they were man eating flowers and got one and pretended to make them eat me and everyone started laughing, even I did. Then we went down into the Arena and there were muddy slopes and David Jones slipped down and got muddy.
